Pink Sapphire Ring
Sterling Silver Jewelry
Size (US) 8

Sapphire has many colors and pink is one of them.
Usually sapphire means blue, but it has much more colors than we think of - black, gray, clear, green, yellow, orange, pink, purple,,,,, and color change.
Those are all natural colors.
And, red sapphire is called ruby. That means this stone (pink sapphire), blue sapphire, and ruby are all the same stone😙

Now all rings are 15% off including this one. Visit my Etsy store!

Battery replacement 
on a rotary tool 

I’ve been using this tool for 2 years I think. Almost everyday, mainly for polishing.
The battery life was getting shorter and shorter, and finally it lasted like only for a few minutes so I switched to an old one - not cordless, heavy tool.
Then, again, my husband. He said the battery could be replaceable, and started researching, ordered a new battery, and he did😳
The socket on the new battery was not the same as the one in the tool, so he cut the wires and soldered them to the other wires, then done! It started working like new again!
I had no idea what to do but maybe I should try it by myself 2 years later….?

Rotary tool : WEN 23072

Spider
Black Jade, Hematite, Labradorite Pendant 
Sterling Silver Jewelry

He is solid sterling silver. 
Do you have a metal allergy?
Since I have a nickel allergy I’m being careful to choose metals, and I’m hearing about metal allergies from customers. I’m not a doctor, I don’t know much about allergies but it's interesting to learn some people prefer sterling, some copper. I know not everyone does allergy tests though, they know their reactions well and choose whatever is safe for them.

I've heard oxidized metal could sometimes be a cause of trouble. Many of my jewelry has been antiqued and polished like this spider, but If you'd prefer not-antiquated metal for your skin I could make the same design without the antique process. (Depends on the design... ask me!)
Or if you'd like to make sure if the piece is antiqued or not, please send me a message.

You know I'm always touching stones (they are called healing crystals right?) but they never worked for my poor fingers and toes... cry... or maybe they are working not to make them worse?? I'd rather think positive way.

Some crystal websites mention that amethyst helps heal skin issues. Should I try to wear an amethyst during winter and see how it works for my fingers and toes🤔

I'm hoping you won't get frostbites. It's not fun at all. Stay warm (and get an amethyst💜)!

How to make a bullet pendant

Here is the way I make the bullet pendant necklaces.
Cut the bullet shell, sand it, and drill the top.
Carefully put the crystal into the shell, then make a bail.
Very simple process! (Just a time consumer😇)

Sterling Silver Jewelry

Can you see the beautiful green in the stone?
Moss agate does not contain moss, but it does look like moss.
According to Wikipedia, “The field is a clear or milky-white quartz, and the included minerals are mainly oxides of manganese or iron. It is not a true form of agate, because it does not have concentric banding.”
It will be a perfect gift for anyone who loves the outdoors!

Since I made this as a practice piece, the price is very reasonable.
